climbs.name: PB is a little brown dog

content.description: Chossy little dome located along the left wall of corridor close to the entrance. A few slopes up to a loose hourglass shaped pinch that will soon fall off (be careful!). Once it falls off it will hopefully become a nice crimp. After this you could use the upwards converging arÃªtes or maybe a layback onto the left wall or use the off-width crack that separates the dome from the wall. Climb down the back.
This crack climbs starts in the gray colored dihedral of sorts, jogs right under a mini roof and continues up the crux hand crack to the top.  There is a mystery bolt at the beginning of the route.

This can be described as a top rope variation to Handsaw.  Right of Handsaw's start is a face with a thin right leaning crack.  Climb this until it is possible to jog left.  From here continue up to the top of via the upper hand crack portion of

Handsaw

.
content.location: Left hand side of Jumbo Rocks Corridor, 10 feet right of the gray dihedral of Handsaw.

climbs.name: Carnage
climbs.fa: FA: Keith Cunning and Ed Kaufer, 1980.

content.description:
This route lies about 50 feet into the narrow section of the corridor, on your left side.  This crack system runs all the way up the wall and is thinner than it might first seem. It is the first route to the left of Mere Illusion (a face past 3 bolts to a thin crack).

Climb up into a concave section (hands), then exit this into a thin hands section (crux). Above the crack widens to a "highly textured" hand crack that can wreck "carnage" if your jamming technique is not perfect....
content.protection: Take a number of cams from .5 to 3 inches.
